WEBVTT

00:02.569 --> 00:05.237
WHEN ARTHUR CHILDRENS
FOUNDED THIS HOSPITAL,

00:05.239 --> 00:07.606
HE HAD AN ILLEGITIMATE SON
THAT HE KEPT HIDDEN

00:07.608 --> 00:09.508
FROM THE HOSPITAL GENTRY
AT THAT TIME.

00:09.510 --> 00:12.444
FOR I AM NOT VALERIE FLAME...

00:12.446 --> 00:14.046
[ Man's voice ]
I'M DERRICK CHILDRENS!

00:14.048 --> 00:15.381
[ ALL GASP ]
-WHAT?!

00:15.383 --> 00:18.350
LONG-LOST SON
OF ARTHUR CHILDRENS.

00:18.352 --> 00:21.520
[ MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

00:23.056 --> 00:24.356
CLAMP.

00:24.358 --> 00:27.526
ALL RIGHT, KID,
COME ON, STAY WITH ME.

00:27.528 --> 00:31.030
AND WE GOT IT.
HE'S GONNA MAKE IT.

00:31.032 --> 00:32.564
[ BELL DINGING ]

00:32.566 --> 00:34.366
IT'S OUR
ONE MILLIONTH PATIENT!

00:34.368 --> 00:37.436
HEY!

00:37.438 --> 00:40.239
[ FLATLINE ]

00:40.241 --> 00:43.575
♪♪

00:48.381 --> 00:49.848
Dr. Kriete: GOD,
YOU'RE SO GORGEOUS, VAL.

00:49.850 --> 00:52.451
IF YOU WERE A MAN, I WOULD
SCISSOR YOU RIGHT NOW.

00:52.453 --> 00:54.453
HOW DO YOU DO IT?

00:54.455 --> 00:56.855
HOWEVER I DID IT,
I DON'T ANYMORE.

00:56.857 --> 01:00.459
I SPENT SO MUCH TIME
PRETENDING TO BE SOMEONE ELSE,

01:00.461 --> 01:03.595
I LOST WHO I REALLY AM.

01:03.597 --> 01:05.030
THAT ENDS TODAY.

01:05.032 --> 01:06.799
[ GASPS ]

01:06.801 --> 01:08.734
Woman:
WHAT'S WRONG WITH MY SON?

01:08.736 --> 01:11.203
Lola: I'VE NEVER SEEN SYMPTOMS
LIKE THIS.

01:11.205 --> 01:13.472
I JUST WISH MY COLLEAGUE,
DR. VALERIE FLAME, WERE HERE.

01:13.474 --> 01:14.673
IT'S HER SPECIALTY.

01:14.675 --> 01:16.809
BUT I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHERE SHE IS.

01:16.811 --> 01:18.977
I DO EVEN
KNOW WHERE SHE IS.

01:18.979 --> 01:20.179
GONE.

01:20.181 --> 01:21.647
NEVER TO RETURN.

01:21.649 --> 01:22.948
WE'LL SAVE YOUR SON.

01:22.950 --> 01:25.918
NO MYSTERY IS TOO TOUGH
FOR DERRICK CHILDRENS.

01:25.920 --> 01:27.152
BRING ME UP-TO-DATE.

01:27.154 --> 01:28.520
YOU BRING <i> ME</i> UP-TO-DATE.

01:28.522 --> 01:30.556
BETTER YET,
BRING ME <i> ON</i> A DATE.

01:30.558 --> 01:33.192
KNOW WHAT I MEAN?
HUBBA HUBBA.

01:33.194 --> 01:34.526
BUT SERIOUSLY, THOUGH,

01:34.528 --> 01:36.295
WHAT IS WITH
THE NEW ADAM'S APPLE AND STUFF?

01:36.297 --> 01:37.863
THIS ISN'T ABOUT ME,
LOLA.

01:37.865 --> 01:40.466
IT DOESN'T MATTER IF I LOOK LIKE
A PLATINUM-BLOND CREAM MACHINE

01:40.468 --> 01:42.534
OR A SMOLDERING HUNK
OF MIDWESTERN BEEFCAKE.

01:42.536 --> 01:44.103
THE PATIENT COMES FIRST.

01:44.105 --> 01:46.438
I'M ORDERING A BATTERY OF TESTS
TO GET TO THE BOTTOM OF THIS.

01:46.440 --> 01:48.173
DORI, ORDER ME
A BATTERY OF TESTS

01:48.175 --> 01:49.441
TO GET TO THE BOTTOM OF THAT.

01:49.443 --> 01:50.676
ABSOLUTELY.

01:50.678 --> 01:52.845
RIGHT AFTER I FINISH
MY JIGSAW PUZZLE.

01:52.847 --> 01:53.879
THANK YOU.

01:53.881 --> 01:55.681
YOU GUYS KNOW
HOW MUCH I LOVE MY JIGGIES!

01:55.683 --> 01:57.816
DORI! EVERY MOMENT YOU WASTE
WAXING POETIC ABOUT

01:57.818 --> 01:59.384
HOW MUCH YOU LOVE
YOUR JIGSAW PUZZLES

01:59.386 --> 02:01.954
IS A MOMENT YOU COULD BE
SPENDING ON YOUR JIGSAW PUZZLE!

02:01.956 --> 02:04.556
YES, DOCTOR.
I'LL START WITH THE EDGES.

02:04.558 --> 02:06.558
GOOD.

02:06.560 --> 02:09.328
SO, WHAT DO YOU MAKE
OF ATTICUS'S SYMPTOMS?

02:09.330 --> 02:10.329
SYMPTOMS?

02:10.330 --> 02:11.563
YEAH.

02:11.565 --> 02:12.798
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
HE HAD SYMPTOMS.

02:12.800 --> 02:14.500
OH.
MY GOD, IT'S BACK.

02:14.502 --> 02:15.501
WHAT'S BACK?

02:15.503 --> 02:18.103
THE PANDEMIC.

02:18.105 --> 02:21.707
100 YEARS AGO, A MYSTERIOUS
ILLNESS BURNED THROUGH CHILDRENS

02:21.709 --> 02:23.742
LIKE WILDFIRE
THROUGH CHILDREN.

02:23.744 --> 02:26.044
NOTHING MY FATHER DID
COULD SAVE THEM.

02:26.046 --> 02:30.249
ALL HOPE SEEMED LOST,
UNTIL...

02:30.251 --> 02:31.650
IT WAS OVER.

02:31.652 --> 02:33.485
HE FOUND THE CURE?
THAT'S CORRECT.

02:33.487 --> 02:35.654
FEARING PANIC,
HE COVERED UP THE OUTBREAK

02:35.656 --> 02:37.923
AND HID THE CURE
SOMEWHERE IN THE HOSPITAL.

02:37.925 --> 02:39.658
SOMEWHERE IN THE HOSPITAL?

02:39.660 --> 02:42.127
BUT THIS PLACE
IS AS BIG AS A BUILDING.

02:42.129 --> 02:44.463
I HAVE A FEELING
I KNOW WHERE HE HID THE CURE.

02:44.465 --> 02:45.864
AND IF MY FEELING
IS CORRECT,

02:45.866 --> 02:48.300
I'M GOING TO SHOW YOU
WHERE THAT PLACE IS NOW.

02:49.702 --> 02:52.638
[ CLATTERING ]

02:56.109 --> 02:57.276
MY FATHER'S OFFICE.

02:57.278 --> 02:59.745
FOR YEARS, IT WAS USED
AS A DUSTY OLD ROOM

02:59.747 --> 03:01.647
FULL OF OLD-FASHIONED
PROPS.

03:01.649 --> 03:03.282
THERE MUST BE A CLUE
IN HERE SOMEWHERE.

03:03.284 --> 03:04.716
YEAH.

03:06.619 --> 03:07.953
[ BLOWS ]

03:07.955 --> 03:09.555
FATHER.

03:09.557 --> 03:10.989
AW, COME, NOW.

03:10.991 --> 03:14.393
AW, YOU REST YOUR HEAD
RIGHT ON MY SHOULDER.

03:14.395 --> 03:19.031
YOU LET YOUR HOT TEARS DRIP
ALL OVER MY THIRSTY MELONS, YES.

03:19.033 --> 03:21.033
COULD YOU JUST GIVE ME
A-A MINUTE?

03:21.035 --> 03:22.434
MM-HMM.

03:22.436 --> 03:24.836
I'm right here.

03:24.838 --> 03:28.140
TELL ME YOUR SECRETS.

03:28.142 --> 03:29.107
OKAY.

03:29.109 --> 03:31.109
I THINK NUMBERS
HAVE GENDERS.

03:31.111 --> 03:32.044
LIKE, 1 IS A BOY.

03:32.046 --> 03:33.679
2 IS A BOY.
BUT 3 IS A GIRL.

03:33.681 --> 03:35.981
4 IS A --
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

03:35.983 --> 03:37.950
WH-- UM...

03:37.952 --> 03:39.184
OH.

03:39.186 --> 03:40.519
ALMOST THERE.

03:40.521 --> 03:42.621
BLAKE, BE READY TO HOLD
THAT UMBRELLA OVER HER BODY

03:42.623 --> 03:44.957
TO PROTECT HER
FROM THE CONFETTI, OKAY?

03:44.959 --> 03:46.124
READY.

03:46.126 --> 03:49.328
AND WE GOT IT.
SHE'S GONNA MAKE IT.

03:49.330 --> 03:51.330
[ BELL DINGING ]

03:51.332 --> 03:54.132
1 MILLION PATIENTS SAVED!

03:55.668 --> 03:57.169
[ FLATLINE ]

03:57.171 --> 03:59.104
WHAT THE HELL, BLAKE?

03:59.106 --> 04:00.772
OKAY, FOR THE RECORD,

04:00.774 --> 04:05.143
YOU NEVER SPECIFICALLY SAID
TO OPEN THE UMBRELLA.

04:06.746 --> 04:08.280
THERE'S NOTHING HERE.

04:08.282 --> 04:09.448
WE LOOKED EVERYWHERE.

04:09.450 --> 04:11.283
HEY.

04:11.285 --> 04:12.684
WHAT ABOUT THIS?

04:12.686 --> 04:14.186
A TARP.

04:14.188 --> 04:15.821
THAT'S A CLUE.

04:15.823 --> 04:19.156
WHAT COULD MY FATHER HAVE MEANT
BY A TARP?

04:19.159 --> 04:21.692
WHAT IF
WE LOOKED UNDER IT?

04:21.695 --> 04:23.662
WHY WOULD WE LOOK
UNDER THE CLUE?

04:25.131 --> 04:27.132
[ GASPS ]

04:28.067 --> 04:30.469
[ FILM PROJECTOR CLICKING ]
FATHER.

04:30.471 --> 04:34.373
<i>IF YOU'RE WATCHING THIS,</i>
<i>THE PANDEMIC HAS RETURNED.</i>

04:34.375 --> 04:39.645
<i>THE CURE IS HIDDEN DEEP</i>
<i>IN THE BOWELS OF CHILDRENS.</i>

04:39.647 --> 04:42.047
<i>NOW, LISTEN CLOSELY.</i>

04:42.049 --> 04:44.316
<i>THIS NEXT PART</i>
<i>IS EXTREMELY IMPOR--</i>

04:44.318 --> 04:47.152
GOT IT!
LET'S GO!

04:47.154 --> 04:49.855
OUT HERE, THE BREEZE WILL BLOW
THE CONFETTI

04:49.857 --> 04:51.356
AWAY FROM THE PATIENT.

04:51.358 --> 04:53.292
CLAMP.

04:54.794 --> 04:58.263
ALL RIGHT.
AND, SUCCESS!

04:58.265 --> 04:59.131
WHOO!

04:59.133 --> 05:00.499
[ BELL DINGING ]
[ LAUGHTER ]

05:00.501 --> 05:02.701
Beth:
1 MILLION PATIENTS SAVED!

05:02.703 --> 05:05.804
[ CHEERING ]

05:05.806 --> 05:07.506
WELL,
THAT DOES IT, RIGHT?

05:07.508 --> 05:08.774
OH!

05:08.776 --> 05:10.642
[ FLATLINE ]
[ BOY SPEAKING SPANISH ]

05:10.644 --> 05:12.911
COME ON!

05:14.380 --> 05:17.716
NO FAIR! LOOK --
YOU HAVE A TON ALREADY!

05:19.686 --> 05:21.486
MY FATHER'S
OLD OPERATING THEATER.

05:21.488 --> 05:24.890
I USED TO PLAY DOWN HERE
BY MYSELF FOR HOURS ON END.

05:24.892 --> 05:26.291
YOU DIDN'T HAVE
ANY FRIENDS?

05:26.293 --> 05:27.292
NO.

05:27.294 --> 05:28.527
WELL, ONE.

05:28.529 --> 05:31.029
AN OLD VAGRANT NAMED TODD
WHO USED TO LIVE DOWN HERE.

05:31.031 --> 05:34.032
HE TAUGHT ME
HOW TO MASTURBATE RIGHT THERE.

05:34.600 --> 05:36.134
[ GASPS ] LOOK!

05:36.136 --> 05:37.703
FATHER.

05:37.705 --> 05:39.371
OH, YOU LET ME KNOW
IF YOU NEED A TISSUE

05:39.373 --> 05:40.605
MADE OUT OF BOOBS, OKAY?

05:40.607 --> 05:42.007
FATHER.

05:42.009 --> 05:43.642
OH, COME BLOW YOUR NOSE
ON MY TITTIES!

05:43.644 --> 05:45.777
[ GRUNTS ]

05:50.149 --> 05:52.918
OOH!
YOUR BUTT SKIN IS SO SOFT.

05:52.920 --> 05:54.386
A WOMAN HAS TO SHAVE.

05:54.388 --> 05:55.654
YEAH. AH.

05:55.656 --> 05:57.322
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
WITH YOUR FINGERS?

05:57.324 --> 05:59.658
I WANT TO WEAR YOU
LIKE A MUPPET.

05:59.660 --> 06:00.726
OSCAR THE GROUCH.

06:00.728 --> 06:02.160
YEAH.

06:02.162 --> 06:04.363
OOH, THERE'S PLENTY OF ROOM
IN MY FILTHY GARBAGE CAN.

06:04.365 --> 06:05.364
YEAH. [ GASPS ]

06:05.366 --> 06:06.365
OH, MY GOD!

06:06.367 --> 06:07.366
THAT'S IT!
I'VE GOT IT!

06:07.368 --> 06:08.867
SERIOUSLY?
WHAT DID I LEAVE IN THERE?

06:08.869 --> 06:11.837
YOUR FATHER --
IN THE FILM, HE DIDN'T SAY,

06:11.839 --> 06:14.406
"IN THE BOWELS
OF CHILDRENS HOSPITAL."

06:14.408 --> 06:18.009
HE SAID,
"IN THE BOWELS OF CHILDRENS."

06:18.011 --> 06:23.749
THAT CURE IS SOMEWHERE
UP INSIDE YOUR DEAD DAD'S BUTT.

06:26.386 --> 06:28.553
BLAKE, KEEP THAT DRONE
AWAY FROM US.

06:28.555 --> 06:30.322
I GOT IT.
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

06:30.324 --> 06:32.491
WE DID IT!

06:32.493 --> 06:34.593
[ BELL DINGING ]
1 MILLION SAVED!

06:34.595 --> 06:36.862
WE DID IT.

06:36.864 --> 06:38.663
[ BARKING ]
[ FLATLINE ]

06:38.665 --> 06:40.298
Woman #2:
DAISY, GET OUT OF THERE.

06:40.300 --> 06:42.401
UGH.

06:44.937 --> 06:46.571
AND WE DID IT!

06:46.573 --> 06:48.306
[ BELL DINGING ]

06:48.308 --> 06:50.909
WHOO!

06:50.911 --> 06:55.313
[ FLATLINE ]

06:55.315 --> 06:58.750
♪♪

06:58.752 --> 07:01.052
AND WE DID IT!

07:01.054 --> 07:03.355
[ BELL DINGING ]
1 MILLION SAVED!

07:04.657 --> 07:06.458
[ FLATLINE ]
AW.

07:06.460 --> 07:09.494
OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT,
THAT'S IT FOR ME. LATER.

07:10.863 --> 07:12.164
THERE'S NOTHING THERE.

07:12.166 --> 07:14.299
IT WOULD BE FASTER
IF I HAD SOME HELP.

07:14.301 --> 07:16.468
I'M NOT STICKING MY ARM
UP MY DEAD DAD'S A-NOOSE!

07:16.470 --> 07:19.104
[ GASPS ]

07:23.776 --> 07:25.143
"IF YOU ARE READING THIS,

07:25.145 --> 07:28.013
YOU PROBABLY DID NOT WATCH
THE WHOLE FILM."

07:30.716 --> 07:33.218
<i>...IS EXTREMELY IMPORTANT.</i>

07:33.220 --> 07:36.822
<i>IT IS "BITAL"</i>
<i>THAT YOU LOOK "BIGILENTLY."</i>

07:36.824 --> 07:38.457
<i>THANK YOU "BERY" MUCH</i>

07:38.459 --> 07:41.493
<i>FOR "BIEWING" THIS FILM</i>
<i>FROM THE "ARCHIBES."</i>

07:41.495 --> 07:42.594
OF COURSE!

07:42.596 --> 07:44.796
MY FATHER HAD
A SPEECH IMPEDIMENT.

07:44.798 --> 07:46.465
HE PRONOUNCED
HIS V's AS B's.

07:46.467 --> 07:49.468
THAT MEANS THE CLUE ISN'T
IN THE <i> BOWELS</i> OF CHILDRENS.

07:49.470 --> 07:52.737
IT'S IN THE <i> VOWELS</i>
OF CHILDRENS.

07:52.739 --> 07:54.806
WHY?
SOMETIMES,

07:54.808 --> 07:57.309
BUT MOSTLY A-E-I-O-U.

08:01.881 --> 08:04.583
THE VOWELS OF CHILDRENS.

08:04.585 --> 08:08.086
♪♪

08:11.791 --> 08:13.291
I THOUGHT I HEARD
WHAT SOUNDED LIKE

08:13.293 --> 08:14.926
A GOOD OLD-FASHIONED
PUZZLE DUMP.

08:14.928 --> 08:16.695
DORI, YOU HAVE TO SOLVE
THIS PUZZLE!

08:16.697 --> 08:19.030
SURE.
RIGHT AWAY, DOCTOR.

08:19.966 --> 08:22.000
QUALITY CONSTRUCTION.

08:22.002 --> 08:23.301
CLEAN EDGES.

08:23.303 --> 08:24.569
OOH, A WHIMSY!

08:24.571 --> 08:26.605
DORI!
SORRY.

08:26.607 --> 08:29.641
♪♪

08:36.115 --> 08:38.383
IT'S JUST ARTHUR CHILDRENS
HOLDING SOME UGLY BABY.

08:38.385 --> 08:41.453
THAT'S NOT
JUST SOME UGLY BABY.

08:41.455 --> 08:43.054
THAT'S <i> ME</i> UGLY BABY.

08:43.056 --> 08:47.125
DERRICK, YOU'RE THE CURE.

08:47.127 --> 08:49.561
TODD THE VAGRANT ALWAYS SAID
I WAS SPECIAL.

08:49.563 --> 08:51.930
LET'S GO SAVE US A KID.

08:55.167 --> 08:56.401
OOF!

08:56.403 --> 08:58.136
IT'S ABOUT TIME.
WE'RE ABOUT TO LOSE ATTICUS.

08:58.138 --> 09:00.338
LET DERRICK IN!
HE CAN SAVE HIM!

09:01.741 --> 09:03.842
[ MOUTHS "THANK YOU" ]

09:03.844 --> 09:06.511
[ MOUTHS "THANK <i> YOU"</i> ]

09:06.513 --> 09:08.780
[ MOUTHS "FOR WHAT?" ]

09:08.782 --> 09:11.283
[ MOUTHS "FOR EVERYTHING" ]

09:11.285 --> 09:13.051
[ FLATLINE ]
[ GASPS ]

09:13.053 --> 09:15.620
WOW. NEXT TIME,
SAVE THE DRAMA FOR YOUR MAMA.

09:15.622 --> 09:20.058
NO! NO!

09:20.060 --> 09:24.496
[ WEEPING ]

09:24.498 --> 09:27.265
WAIT A MINUTE.
WE'VE GOT A PULSE.

09:27.267 --> 09:29.200
[ GASPS ] DERRICK!
IT'S YOUR TEARS!

09:29.202 --> 09:30.602
YOUR TEARS ARE THE CURE!

09:30.604 --> 09:31.670
WHAT?

09:31.672 --> 09:32.938
-OH, MY GOD!
-OH, MY GOD!

09:32.940 --> 09:34.606
YOU'RE DOING IT, DERRICK!
YOU'RE MAGIC!

09:34.608 --> 09:35.774
STOP COMPLIMENTING ME!

09:35.776 --> 09:37.309
SAY SAD THINGS!
I'M DRYING UP.

09:37.311 --> 09:39.711
KIDS GROW UP SO FAST.
OH!

09:39.713 --> 09:41.513
C-C-CUTTING ONIONS!

09:41.515 --> 09:43.114
LAURA LINNEY
HAS NEVER WON AN OSCAR.

09:43.116 --> 09:45.083
[ WEEPING ]

09:45.085 --> 09:47.085
HE'S GONNA MAKE IT!

09:47.087 --> 09:48.353
[ SNIFFLES ]

09:48.355 --> 09:51.323
[ BELL DINGING ]

09:51.325 --> 09:53.959
1 MILLION PATIENTS SAVED!

09:53.961 --> 09:55.393
[ GASPS ] UH-OH.

09:55.395 --> 09:57.629
RELAX --
THOUGHT THIS MIGHT HAPPEN.

09:57.631 --> 10:00.365
SO WHAT I DID WAS
I LAMINATED THE CONFETTI

10:00.367 --> 10:03.435
INTO ONE BIG, SOLID,
SURPRISINGLY HEAVY BALL OF --

10:03.437 --> 10:04.536
[ SQUISH ]

10:04.538 --> 10:07.105
[ FLATLINE ]

10:09.942 --> 10:13.378
DO YOU HAVE TO GO?
YOU KNOW THAT I DO.

10:13.380 --> 10:16.448
WELL, I'LL MISS YOU,
DERRICK CHILDRENS.

10:16.450 --> 10:19.751
♪♪

10:21.587 --> 10:23.154
SO, WHERE WILL YOU GO?

10:23.156 --> 10:24.856
I'M GONNA HIT THE ROAD
WITH AN OLD FRIEND.

10:24.858 --> 10:26.791
[ SHOPPING CART RATTLES ]

10:26.793 --> 10:28.259
OH.

10:28.261 --> 10:30.462
TAKE CARE OF HIM,
TODD THE VAGRANT.

10:30.464 --> 10:31.896
TAKE CARE OF <i> HIM?</i>

10:31.898 --> 10:33.765
HE'S GOT MAGIC TEARS!

10:33.767 --> 10:35.834
WE'RE JOINING THE CIRCUS!

10:35.836 --> 10:37.869
I'M GONNA KEEP YOU
IN A CAGE.

10:37.871 --> 10:39.871
[ LAUGHS ]

10:39.873 --> 10:41.006
FUN.

10:41.008 --> 10:44.109
♪♪

10:44.810 --> 10:47.412
♪ I'M BRINGING
ALL MY HAT TRICKS ♪

10:47.414 --> 10:49.447
♪ I'M USING SLEIGHT OF HAND ♪

10:49.449 --> 10:51.616
♪ BOUNCE BACK LIKE I'M ELASTIC ♪

10:51.618 --> 10:53.818
♪ I FEEL GOOD,
I'M FEELING GRAND ♪

10:53.820 --> 10:56.021
♪ IN THE SPOTLIGHT,
IN THE SPOTLIGHT ♪

10:56.023 --> 10:58.123
♪ MAKE THE STARS SHINE ♪

10:58.125 --> 10:59.424
♪ HEY ♪

10:59.426 --> 11:01.426
♪ I GOT THE MAGIC ♪

11:01.428 --> 11:04.162
♪ YEAH, I'M THE BEST ♪

11:04.164 --> 11:06.398
♪ IN THE PACK ♪

11:06.400 --> 11:07.432
♪ YEAH ♪

11:07.434 --> 11:08.833
Sal: <i> ATTENTION, STAFF.</i>

11:08.835 --> 11:09.968
<i>HOO-HOO.</i>

11:09.970 --> 11:11.236
<i>THAT IS OWL.</i>
